<p>sed - stream editor</p>

<p>A stream editor is used to perform basic text transformations on an input stream (a file or input from a pipeline).</p>

<p>To replace text in a file:</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>sed 's/\t//g' 1.txt &gt; 2.txt
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Above is replacing every tab â€œ\tâ€ on the line because we use the â€œgâ€ for global, with nothing so deleting the tabs in the file.</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>sed 's/\t/A/' 1.txt &gt; 2.txt
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Above replaces only the first tab on the line with a â€œAâ€.</p>

